%h4 Strong and Emphasize

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      *emphasize*   **strong**
      _emphasize_   __strong__
%br

%h4 Links and Email

%p Inline:

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      An [example](http://url.com/ "Title")

%p Reference-style labels (titles are optional):

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      An [example][id]. Then, anywhere
      else in the doc, define the link:

        [id]: http://example.com/  "Title"

%p Email:

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      An email <example@example.com> link.
%br

%h4 Images

%p Inline (titles are optional):

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      ![alt text](/path/img.jpg "Title")

%p Reference-style:

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      ![alt text][id]
      [id]: /url/to/img.jpg "Title"
%br

%h4 Headers

%p Setext-style:

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      Header 1
      ========

      Header 2
      --------

%p atx-style (closing #’s are optional):

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      # Header 1 #

      ## Header 2 ##

      ###### Header 6
%br

%h4 Lists

%p Ordered, without paragraphs:

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      1.  Foo
      2.  Bar

%p Unordered, with paragraphs:

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      *   A list item.

          With multiple paragraphs.

      *   Bar

%p You can nest them:

%pre
  %code
    :preserve
      *   Abacus
          * answer
      *   Bubbles
          1.  bunk
          2.  bupkis
              * BELITTLER
          3. burper
      *   Cunning
%br

